 5. Data Engineering

 Batch vs Stream Processing
- Batch: Process large volumes at once (e.g., Hadoop MapReduce, Spark batch).
- Stream: Process data in real-time as it arrives (Kafka Streams, Flink, Spark Streaming).

 Lambda vs Kappa Architecture
- Lambda: Two pipelines – batch (accurate, slow) + speed (real-time, approximate). Merge later. (Complex maintenance.)
- Kappa: Single stream pipeline. Use Kafka for replay (treat stream as source of truth). Simpler, modern default.

Example: Netflix recommendations use Kappa for real-time personalization.

