 Phase 7: How to Draw & Document Architecture

 7.1 Standard Diagram Components (C4 Model)
1.  Context (Level 1): The big picture (User -> System -> External services).
2.  Container (Level 2): High-level tech (Web App, Mobile App, Database, Message Queue).
3.  Component (Level 3): Inside a container (Controllers, Services, Repositories).
4.  Code (Level 4): Class diagrams (rarely drawn).

 7.2 Common Notations
- Box: A service/component.
- Arrow (solid): Synchronous API call (REST/gRPC).
- Arrow (dashed): Asynchronous event/message.
- Database cylinder: Storage.
- Cloud icon: External third-party (AWS S3, Twilio).

 7.3 Questions to ask when reviewing architecture
- What happens if this server dies?
- Can this handle 10x the traffic next month?
- What is the worst-case latency (p99)?
- How do we deploy a change without downtime? (Blue/Green or Canary deployment)

