 Final Learning Roadmap

| Level | Focus | Practice Project |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| Beginner | One server, one DB, no caching | Build a simple blog API (Flask/Express + Postgres). Deploy on a single VM. |
| Intermediate | Add load balancer, cache, separate read/write | Add Redis cache. Split DB into primary + replica. Deploy with Docker Compose. |
| Advanced | Microservices, message queue, sharding | Build a URL shortener (2 services: `auth` + `shortener`). Use Kafka for analytics. Shard by `user_id`. |
| Expert | Consensus, event sourcing, service mesh | Implement a distributed counter using Raft (etcd). Build an event-sourced shopping cart. |

Key Takeaway: There is no "perfect" architecture. Every decision is a trade-off between:
- Consistency vs. Availability (CAP Theorem)
- Speed vs. Cost
- Simplicity vs. Flexibility

Great architects understand the business requirements first, then choose the right set of trade-offs.
